A SCP designation shouldn't be in a footnote. The text was much harder to follow as a result.

I'll also second the  would have been more often seen in speculative fiction refering to neutral sapient entities than with persons not conforming to establishment gender roles. Given that clowns can be construed as alien, that is what I took it as, initially. And although dramatic ambiguity is a sought-after trope on this site, the fuzziness at the end didn't sit well with me. I don't think that a scientist would treat noncorporeal sapience with the kind of easily satisfied disinterest displayed here.







